Thyda’s is amazing! They prepare all the meats, pickle all the veggies and make all the salsas in their prep kitchen right next to the stand. Not only is the food delicious but Thyda and Majed are super lovely people. For anyone that needs a quality taco fix I always recommend Thyda’s!

To be honest, I haven't tried the full menu like I want to because I can never quit their burritos.  I am a burrito fanatic and this is hands down my favorite on this island.  The chicken, pork, steak...all fantastic.  I love the added touch of grilling the burrito just slightly so it has a little crisp when you bite into it.  I add the "works" and pair it with their homemade salsas (habanero for the win!)...a great lunch any day of the week.  Call in your order as they can get a huge rush.  But, service is always great and worth the wait.

If your craving for good Mexican food in Honolulu Thyda’s Taco is one of the stops you have to go too.  It’s a small taco truck that make great tacos and burritos from carne asada, beef tongue/lengua, chicken and the surprising jack fruit tacos.  Plus, Majed and Thyda’s crew will take care of you.  Don’t forget to request for all three of their sauces.

Bottom line: great food at an unbeatable price. Done. If you want Cali/Texas quality Mexican food in Hawaii without breaking the bank, come here.

Simply amazing. Barbacoa mulita is like a baby quesadilla with diced white onion. Crisp tortillas encase a unctuous combo of shredded beef cheeks in Monterey cheese. A mix of their roasted salsa roja and tomatillo salsa verde make the perfect condiment! Friendly folks and it sounds like they have many regulars. I'll be one of them.

We were staying across the street and were looking for a fast, delicious lunch.  This hit the spot.  My party ordered rice bowls, burritos and a quesadilla.  All were delicious.  The restauranteurs were super friendly as they cooked our meals.  They have a nice variety of hot sauces to self serve.  You could park in the whole foods parking deck, grab your food here and eat where ever you wanted as it's a food stand, no seating.  Reasonable prices.

Great little taco spot on the mauka side of the new whole foods in Kakaako, across the street from the parking garage entrance to Whole Foods. ... One of the only taco spots on oahu that serves tacos with all the fixings, including raddish, grilled onions, lime, and pickled jalepenos. The taco prices are about average for Honolulu which in general is pretty high for example three tacos, 1-pollo, 1-carne asada, and 1-carnitas came out to $9.25. Solid tacos would return and would recommend. Small area with little shade and no real place to eat. There is a small bench but best to expect to eat standing up or take it to go and find somewhere near by.

Cool Mexican (Cali style) trailer/shack across from whole foods. They have a good variety of menu options and meats as well as a jackfruit option. I've had the jackfruit burrito a couple times, it's pretty delicious, albeit a bit on the dry side. Make sure you get salsa. Very friendly service, a little slow at peak lunch time. 11-6 Tu-Sat. (I'm a vegetarian)

I love this place!   A hard to find little trailer set up like a food truck on Queen St near the new construction.  I was walking past this place on my way to a lunch date and could not resist to try one.  That's right, just one. It was delicious and came with all the fixins.  I am hard to please when it comes to Mexican food and this one is a winner.  A little pricey and no where to sit since it is basically a food truck. I will definitely come back and help spread the good word.

I finally had a day off so I could come try this taco truck. It’s located across of Whole Foods on Queen Street. There are a couple of stalls in front of the taco truck but parking really sucks there. I parked at Ward and walked over. The good thing is, I came on Taco Tuesday so tacos were $2-$2.50. They have tons of proteins to choose from:  Pollo Carnitas Asada Barbacoa Jackfruit (only vegetarian option) Lengua  We got one of each! The tacos are served with limes, radish and some spicy veggies. The tacos were delicious. It’s hard to say which was my favorite but I would have to say the lengua. The lengua chunks were tender and flavorful.  They also have 3 sauces to choose. I got the green one which is the least spicy and I could handle.  I never heard of a mulita so I got one to try. It’s basically a taco and quesadilla in one. A flat fried taco. It was interesting but I think I prefer regular tacos. Definitely one of the best taco places I’ve been to here.
I'm addicted to their burritos and hot sauce!
